<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/24038029-jennifer-kennedy"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1379470253i/24038029._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/24038029-jennifer-kennedy">Jennifer Kennedy</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Bevins wanted to appreciate living on earth with all of his senses and regretted not doing so while he was living. So, his sensory organs are multipli<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Bevins wanted to appreciate living on earth with all of his senses and regretted not doing so while he was living. So, his sensory organs are multiplied in the Bardo as a warped manifestation of his wishes. The reverend and all of the characters in the Bardo do not admit to having made any mistakes, or they at least come up with justifications for their mistakes they made while living. So, they can't move on until they are truthful with themselves. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
